  "prompt": "How do I reduce lips protrusion without surgery?",
  "response": "Reducing lip protrusion without surgery can be challenging, but there are a few techniques that may help to minimize its appearance temporarily:\n\n1. **Makeup Tricks**:\n   - **Lip Liner**: Use a lip liner slightly inside the natural lip line to create the illusion of smaller lips.\n   - **Dark Lip Colors**: Darker shades tend to make lips look smaller, while lighter shades can make them appear larger.\n   - **Contour**: Apply a matte shadow or bronzer around the edges of your lips and blend well to create the illusion of less protrusion.\n\n2. **Lip Exercises**:\n   Some people believe that certain facial yoga or lip exercises can help tone and reduce lip protrusion. These exercises include:\n   - **Lip Press**: Press your lips together firmly and hold for several seconds, repeating multiple times.\n   - **Smile with Closed Lips**: Try smiling broadly with lips together, stretching the muscles around the mouth.\n\n3. **Avoid Habits that Increase Lip Size**:\n   - If you habitually bite or purse your lips, try to stop these behaviors as they might contribute to swelling or muscle buildup over time.\n\n4. **Hydration**:\n   - Keeping lips well-moisturized can help maintain their natural shape and prevent them from appearing overly large due to dryness and cracking.\n\n5. **Healthy Lifestyle**:\n   - Maintaining overall physical health through proper diet, hydration, and regular exercise can contribute to the health and appearance of your facial muscles and skin.\n\nIt's important to note that significant changes to lip protrusion are typically achieved through medical or cosmetic procedures. If non-surgical options do not produce the desired effect, you may want to consult with a dermatologist or a cosmetic surgeon to explore other possibilities.\n\nRemember, embracing natural features and focusing on overall facial harmony is always a healthy approach!",
